close_reason: Implemented contract-derived pm_copy schema and warning-clean MCP lifecycle coverage; GH-542 will close on PR merge.
body: "The MCP boundary's declared-keys warning (shipped by pm-qxwu via pm-at83) is only trustworthy if each tool's declared surface matches what the runtime actually accepts. pm_copy under-declares: runtime handler spreads args into runAction so flat title/message work, but the schema routes them through nested options — the ONLY narrow mutation tool shaped this way. Evidence in-repo: tests/integration/mcp-dynamic-package-actions.spec.ts ~:1340 passes flat title/message/idOnly and every CI run emits 3 warnings; same suite passes 'text' to pm_close (not a real param, silently ignored — assertion value untested). Class framing: this is the INPUT-side sibling of pm-srns (uniform output contract) and belongs to the mpbb declared-contract-rendering ledger family (6y58/9qcr/ulqu render FROM contract domain; this one DECLARES from contract). Fix in tool-definitions.ts by deriving from COPY_FLAG_CONTRACTS, not by hand-adding keys."
